      <h2>Why I Chose Lakshadweep</h2>
      <p>
        Lakshadweep is a small archipelago off India's southwest coast famous for clear turquoise water, coral reefs and calm lagoons.
        I chose it because it looks peaceful and perfect for water activities like snorkelling and scuba diving â€” a nice break from busy city life.
      </p>

      <h2>Interesting Facts & Activities</h2>
      <p>
        The islands are known for their rich marine life and coral reefs. Popular activities include snorkelling, scuba diving, glass-bottom boat rides, and relaxing on quiet beaches.
        Some islands with visitor facilities are Agatti, Kavaratti, Minicoy and Kadmat. For more official information, you can read about Lakshadweep online. 
        <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lakshadweep" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Learn more about Lakshadweep (Wikipedia)</a>.
      </p>

